<% content_for :title, page_title("Privacy") %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "How Baltimore.ai collects, uses, and protects information." %>

<%= render "shared/breadcrumbs", crumbs: [ [ "Home", root_path ], [ "Privacy", nil ] ] %>

<article class="max-w-2xl">
  <header class="border-b border-stone-200 pb-8 mb-8">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-red-700 font-semibold mb-3">Privacy</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight">Privacy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-stone-500 text-sm">Last updated: <%= Date.today.strftime("%B %Y") %></p>
  </header>

  <div class="prose-editorial">
    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Public listings.</strong> Information about companies, research labs, and resources comes from public sources and (when claimed) from the people who claim those listings.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Account information.</strong> When you claim a listing, we store your email address and an association to the company you claimed. We do not store passwords &mdash; sign-in uses one-time magic links.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Contact form.</strong> When you fill out the contact form, we store your name, email, message, and the IP address and user-agent of the request (for spam protection).
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Analytics.</strong> We may use server-side request logs and aggregate Google Search Console data. We do not currently run third-party analytics scripts.
    </p>

    <h2>What we don't collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Payment card data &mdash; if/when we accept payments, Stripe handles it directly.</li>
      <li>Marketing tracking cookies.</li>
      <li>Information about you from data brokers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we use it</h2>
    <p>
      Listing information is published on the directory. Account information is used to authenticate you and let you edit your claimed listing. Contact-form submissions are used to respond to your message.
    </p>
    <p>
      We don't sell your data. We don't share it with third parties except service providers who help us run the site (email delivery, hosting, payment processing if applicable).
    </p>

    <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Listings:</strong> indefinitely while published; deleted on request.</li>
      <li><strong>Accounts:</strong> as long as you have a claimed listing.</li>
      <li><strong>Contact-form messages:</strong> up to 12 months, then deleted.</li>
      <li><strong>Logs:</strong> 30 days.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You can ask us to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Tell you what we have about you (access).</li>
      <li>Correct it (rectification).</li>
      <li>Delete it (erasure / "right to be forgotten").</li>
      <li>Export it (portability).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Email us via the <a href="<%= contact_path %>">contact form</a> or directly. Response within 30 days.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      Baltimore.ai is not directed to children under 13 and we don't knowingly collect information from them.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If we change this policy materially, we'll update the "Last updated" date above. Substantive changes will be highlighted at the top of this page for at least 30 days.
    </p>

    <h2>Who runs Baltimore.ai</h2>
    <p>
      Justus Eapen. See <a href="<%= root_path %>about">About</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</article>
